.SS "Examples"
.PP
Use a tarball as a starting point for a new repository\&.
.RS 4
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
$ tar zxf frotz\&.tar\&.gz
$ cd frotz
$ git init
$ git add \&. \fB(1)\fR
$ git commit \-m "import of frotz source tree\&."
$ git tag v2\&.43 \fB(2)\fR
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
